	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Frequency of the quartz resonator: MCLK = 26.601712 MHz<br />CPU speed: MCLK/15 = 1.77344746666... MHz</div>
<br />So they did the frequency divider the right way (/15), not the cheap way (/16) that Nintendo chose for the 2A07. That would appear to make it compatible with NTSC cycle-timed code, except for things like (IIRC) Balloon Fight that rely on NMI-to-draw timing instead of sprite 0 or PPU timing and would get tripped up by the extra 50 lines of vblank.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
